
Description
-----------
-Download and extract the kernel source
-Define a new system call sys_hello()
-Add the new system call (sys_hello() ) into the system call table (syscall_64.tbl file)
-Add the hello directory to the kernelâ€™s Makefile
-Add the new system call(sys_hello())  in the system call header file.
-Compile this kernel on your system.
-Run userspace program dmesg to verify.

Reference:
https://tssurya.wordpress.com/2014/08/19/adding-a-hello-world-system-call-to-linux-kernel-3-16-0/

Steps to run the program:
-------------------------

 1.  make
 It will generate a executable file user.

 2. ./user
 To Run executable.  

 3. make clean
 Removes executable.

OUTPUT
-------
1)Check on the terminal
system call sys_hello returned 0

2)Run command: dmesg
[  748.576801] Hello World

